## Conjecture
Option (a) untrack is correct over (b) scrub: .beads/ JSONL files are local
`bd` state synced via `bd dolt push` to a separate Dolt remote, not via git.
Keeping them in git creates a drift-prone second source of truth that leaks
PII into commit history on every `bd sync`.

